    "Related WorkLLMs alignment.",
    "Hendrycks et al. [16] introduced the ETHICS dataset to evaluate LLMs' understanding of ethics, revealing that LLMs have a partial understanding of human ethics but lack comprehensive ethical reasoning capabilities.",
    "While this dataset provides a valuable benchmark, it does not address the challenges of efficiently testing LLMs for safety alignment.",
    "Dai et al. [6] developed Beaver, an open-source RLHF framework that provides training data and reproducible code for alignment studies.",
    "Although Beaver facilitates the training process, it does not focus on optimizing the testing phase, which is the primary concern of our proposed framework."
